    "offer_browser_tts": "false",
    "panels": [
      {
        "text": "#Welcome to the Neighborhood!\n\n- There is a **Painter object** that can move and paint.\n\n- This **grid** is 8 spaces wide and 8 spaces tall.\n\n- There are **obstacles** like the traffic cone, the wall, and the sidewalk that the Painter can't move on or through.",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/3287670f37e9fbb6922f10590c9b6c92-Neighborhood.jpg",
        "key": "test-intro-to-programming-lesson6-level1a-e5d1dd23-d8d1-43e7-bc7b-56f197587f67"
      },
      {
        "text": "#Add the Painter\n- painter  = Painter()\n\n**You can name the painter anything you choose.**\n- bob = Painter()\n- juanita = Painter()\n\nAll of the examples do the same thing. They add a painter object to your neighborhood! ",
        "imageUrl": "",
        "key": "test-intro-to-programming-lesson6-level1a-91cac369-0d9d-46ec-a0a9-e5f5c4ac7380"
      },
      {
        "text": "#Methods the Painter can do include:\n\n- move()\n- turn_left()\n- paint()",
        "imageUrl": "",
        "key": "test-intro-to-programming-lesson6-level1a-21e28908-745a-4f0a-a496-0467aef4bb96"
      },
      {
        "text": "#Attributes the Painter can have include:\n\n- xposition\n- yposition\n- direction",
        "imageUrl": "",
        "key": "test-intro-to-programming-lesson6-level1a-ad3c826c-5ace-4c82-b5b8-f60855fec0ea"
      }
    ]
  },
